# Static Hosting & Image Management

## Core Constraint

Deployed to **GitHub Pages** -- pure static host. Build output (`dist/`) contains JS, CSS, HTML, and optimized images. Everything is self-contained.

## Image Management via Vite Imports

Images in `src/assets/images/` are imported via Vite. All imports centralized in `src/data/imageImports.js`.

### Adding new images

1. Place file in `src/assets/images/` (use hyphens, no spaces)
2. Add import in `src/data/imageImports.js`
3. Add to the appropriate array in `imageData`

### Shared image constants

`allImages` and `STORY_GROUPS` are exported from `imageImports.js` for use across Gallery components and pages.

## Vite Build Configuration

```js
export default defineConfig({
  base: '/trend-studio/',
  build: {
    outDir: 'dist',
    assetsDir: 'assets',
    minify: 'terser'
  }
})
```

`base: '/trend-studio/'` matches the GitHub Pages subpath deployment.

The build copies `index.html` to `404.html` for SPA fallback with BrowserRouter.

## Static SEO Files

- `public/robots.txt` -- crawl rules and sitemap reference
- `public/sitemap.xml` -- static sitemap with all routes

## What Goes Where

| Content | Location | Served From |
|---|---|---|
| JS/CSS/HTML bundles | `dist/assets/` | GitHub Pages |
| Salon images | `dist/assets/` (Vite-processed) | GitHub Pages |
| Google Fonts | Google Fonts CDN | `<link>` in `index.html` |
| Three.js / BAS / GSAP | CDN script tags | `<script>` in `index.html` |
| robots.txt, sitemap.xml | `dist/` (from `public/`) | GitHub Pages |
